spreadsheet.SUM: Adds a series of numbers and/or cells.
spreadsheet.SUMIF: Adds the cells based on specified condition.
spreadsheet.SUMIFS: Adds the cells based on specified conditions.
spreadsheet.ABS: Returns the value of a number without its sign.
spreadsheet.RAND: Returns a random number between 0 and 1.
spreadsheet.RANDBETWEEN: Returns a random integer based on specified values.
spreadsheet.FLOOR: Rounds a number down to the nearest multiple of a given factor.
spreadsheet.CEILING: Rounds a number up to the nearest multiple of a given factor.
spreadsheet.PRODUCT: Multiplies a series of numbers and/or cells.
spreadsheet.AVERAGE: Calculates average for the series of numbers and/or cells excluding text.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEIF: Calculates average for the cells based on specified criterion.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEIFS: Calculates average for the cells based on specified conditions.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEA: Calculates the average for the cells evaluating TRUE as 1, text and FALSE as 0.
spreadsheet.COUNT: Counts the cells that contain numeric values in a range.
spreadsheet.COUNTIF: Counts the cells based on specified condition.
spreadsheet.COUNTIFS: Counts the cells based on specified conditions.
spreadsheet.COUNTA: Counts the cells that contains values in a range.
spreadsheet.MIN: Returns the smallest number of the given arguments.
spreadsheet.MAX: Returns the largest number of the given arguments.
spreadsheet.DATE: Returns the date based on given year, month, and day.
spreadsheet.DAY: Returns the day from the given date.
spreadsheet.DAYS: Returns the number of days between two dates.
spreadsheet.IF: Returns value based on the given expression.
spreadsheet.IFS: Returns value based on the given multiple expressions.
spreadsheet.CalculateAND: Returns TRUE if all the arguments are TRUE, otherwise returns FALSE.
spreadsheet.CalculateOR: Returns TRUE if any of the arguments are TRUE, otherwise returns FALSE.
spreadsheet.IFERROR: Returns value if no error found else it will return specified value.
spreadsheet.CHOOSE: Returns a value from list of values, based on index number.
spreadsheet.INDEX: Returns a value of the cell in a given range based on row and column number.
spreadsheet.FIND: Returns the position of a string within another string, which is case sensitive
spreadsheet.CONCATENATE: Combines two or more strings together.
spreadsheet.CONCAT: Concatenates a list or a range of text strings.
spreadsheet.SUBTOTAL: Returns subtotal for a range using the given function number.
spreadsheet.MATCH: Returns the relative position of a specified value in given range.
